limerick_list.text:
My beauty is ageless, I'm regal;
My glance is like that of an eagle;
Age cannot wither
Nor custom stale either
The infinite charms of a beagle.

This metal shows malleability;
It is strong and has little fragility.
Here in sheets it is spread;
There it's drawn into thread.
As I've said, it has striking ductility.

The arteries carry the blood;
Without them our bodies would flood.
They're elasticized — sorta;
The chief's the aorta.
If it ruptures, that's all for you, Bud!

I adore you, my beautiful spoon worm;
I'd travel for you to the moon, worm.
I find, echiuran,
You're strangely allurin';
With love that's endurin' I swoon, worm!

What's a clinker? A fire room hand;
It's the shackles that convicts can't stand;
It's a baseball miscue;
A hard biscuit you chew;
And an awful off-note from a band.

You're a beast, and I'm gonna discede;
Get away from you — that's what I need.
To remain would be blunder;
My cup runneth under.
Goodbye — I'm a one-man stampede.

It's a desert for Sandgropers (strewth!);
A guitar Zappa played (in my youth);
Or a braveheart called Mel
(Now that must ring a bell!);
Or a cocktail of gin and vermouth.

They open your mail every day;
And they limit the things you can say;
And allowable news
Fits the government's views,
In a censor-y overload way.

My green yard is a great source of pride;
It's well-known, so I hear, far and wide.
I don't need to mow—
Plastic grass doesn't grow;
That is AstroTurf's positive side.

They'd only one hit they could claim;
"She's the One" brought The Chartbusters fame.
This band from D.C.
Only hit 33;
Thus, they didn't live up to their name.

Hindoo dancing girl; French: bayadère;
Bailadeira in Portuguese—they're
English bayadere's source;
This we nowadays force
Into dubbing a striped fabric ware!

Your faineance, Brad, makes us sad;
You're the most slothful son that we've had.
You're always maneuvering,
Blowing off hoovering;
Ass-kicking's next, lazy lad!

"The surface (intended to strike)
Of an implement, tool, or the like;
Or the top of a tooth;
Or a knife's edge: in truth,
These are each called a face," explained Mike.

Irrevocable destiny calls;
We're in thrall to the way the die falls.
It's our lot, it's our fate;
There's a date that can't wait.
It's our doom to succumb to life's squalls.

For my furlough, no way I'll go home;
Leaves of absence I won't spend in Nome!
I'll go topless in Nice,
And in Mykonos, Greece;
Then I'll top off my tops off in Rome.

Deoperculate: omen fulfilled;
The ketchup all over me spilled.
I left off the top;
This really must stop,
Unless by divinity willed.

Three mice on the run, sight-impaired;
One wife of a farmer, not scared.
She strikes from behind,
Decaudation in mind;
Three quick blows, three blind-mouse bottoms bared.

A fiber that's toxic to man;
A substance we're starting to ban;
A mineral mined.
And now I've defined
Asbestos as best as I can.

What's a blackfish? Three stories unfold:
It's a pilot (or black) whale, I'm told;
It's a post-spawning salmon
You might chance to examine;
Or a food-fish that lives in the cold.
